# Colors Contract (Strict Control)

- Global enforcement summary: `design-tokens-units.mdc` (always applied).
- Colors will be provided explicitly by you; do not generate or suggest new colors.
- Do not modify provided colors in `src/styles/tokens/colors.css` unless asked.

## Project palette only

- Components must use Tailwind utilities backed by `src/styles/tokens/colors.css` (`gray-*`, `primary-*`, etc.).
- Do **not** use arbitrary palette utilities that are not part of this file (examples to avoid: default `text-green-500`, `bg-blue-200` from stock Tailwind if those scales are not in `colors.css`).
- Do **not** add a separate semantic alias CSS layer; map UI directly to the documented scales (e.g. `bg-gray-25`, `text-gray-900`, `border-gray-200`, `text-primary-600`).

## No Fallbacks (Critical)

- Do NOT invent hex/rgb in components or one-off palette utilities outside `colors.css`.
- If a required shade or scale is missing from `colors.css`, request it instead of approximating.
